British-born American actor and comedian [[Bob Hope]] had a brief boxing career (in 1919) under the name Packy East (named after the popular boxer [[Packey McFarland]]).<ref name="Boxing-Scoop.com" /> His best result was making it to the finals of the Ohio novice championship in 1919.<ref name="Current Biography 1941" /><ref name="cleveland.com bio" /> Hope participated in a few staged bouts later in life.
