{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox musical artist | honorific_prefix = | name = Mal Blum | honorific_suffix = | image = [[File:Mal Blum June 2015.JPG|220px|Mal Blum in June 2015]] | image_size = | landscape = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank --> | alt = | caption = | background = solo_singer | native_name = | native_name_lang = | birth_name = | alias = | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people supply only the year unless the exact date is already WIDELY published, as per [[WP:DOB]] --> | birth_place = | origin = | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date 1st) --> | death_place = | genre = [[Folk music|Folk]], [[Anti-folk]], [[Rock music|Rock]], [[Punk rock|Punk]] | occupation = Musician, singer-songwriter | instrument = Vocals, guitar | years_active = <!-- YYYY–YYYY (or –present) --> | label = [[Don Giovanni Records]] | associated_acts = | website = {{URL|malblum.com}}
| module = | module2 = | module3 = }}
'''Mal Blum''' (born July 7, 1988) is an American [[songwriter]], musician, writer and performer from New York.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.malblum.com/albums/|title = Mal Blum|publisher = Mal Blum|date = |accessdate = October 22, 2015}}</ref>
They{{efn|Blum is [[non-binary]] and uses they/them pronouns.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Keller|first1=Jessica|title=Hanging Out With Mal Blum|url=http://www.hercampus.com/school/chatham/hanging-out-mal-blum|website=Her Campus}}</ref>}} spent their early career promoting self-booked DIY solo tours.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.malblum.com/ |title=Mal Blum |publisher=Mal Blum |date= |accessdate=December 5, 2013}}</ref>
In 2014, they signed to Don Giovanni records and announced they would be working on a new album produced by Marissa Paternoster of the band [[Screaming Females]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mal Blum Joins Don Giovanni Records|url=http://dongiovannirecords.com/news/mal-blum-joins-don-giovanni-records|website=Don Giovanni Records|language=en}}</ref> Before that point, they had never worked with a [[record label]] and fan-funded or self-funded recording costs.<ref>{{cite web|last=Blum |first=Mal |url=http://malblum.blogspot.com/2013/04/oh-crap-its-been-years-here-is-whats.html |title=MalBlumallbumalbmalbmalummmum: Oh Crap, It's Been Years |publisher=Malblum.blogspot.com |date=April 25, 2013 |accessdate=December 5, 2013}}</ref> After the Don Giovanni release of "You Look a Lot Like Me" in 2015, Blum began touring nationally as a three piece with a bassist and drummer, contributing to what critics called a "more developed but still gritty, punk" sound.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://allstonpudding.com/review-allison-weiss-mal-blum-winter-kid-in-the-attic-dump-him-at-cuisine-en-locale-114/|title=REVIEW: Allison Weiss, Mal Blum, Winter, Kid in the Attic, Dump Him at Cuisine En Locale (11/4) - Allston Pudding|date=November 10, 2015|publisher=}}</ref>
Blum is a recurring musical and non-musical guest on ''[[The Chris Gethard Show]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thechrisgethardshow.com/2012/06/on-tcgs-farewell-melissa-mal-blum/ |title=6/13 on TCGS – Farewell Melissa with Mal Blum |publisher=The Chris Gethard Show |date=June 11, 2012 |accessdate=December 5, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://thechrisgethardshow.tumblr.com/post/35175086753/i-think-we-can-all-agree-that-mal-blum-has-been-a |title=I think we can all agree that Mal Blum has been a... &#124; The Chris Gethard Show |publisher=Thechrisgethardshow.tumblr.com |date= |accessdate=December 5, 2013}}</ref> and has had their music featured on [[Logo TV]]'s [[The Click List: Top 10 Videos]] and NewNowNext Music<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.logotv.com/shows/dyn/the_click_list_2009/videos.jhtml |title=The Click List: 2009 Top 10 Videos &#124; Video Clips, Watch Full Episodes Online |publisher=Logotv.com |date= |accessdate=December 5, 2013}}</ref> They also have appeared as a musical guest on the [[Welcome to Night Vale]] (WTNV) podcast and toured extensively with WTNV live shows in 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last=Merka Nelson |first=Kelly |url=https://www.sacurrent.com/ArtSlut/archives/2017/11/24/welcome-to-night-vale-brings-eldritch-weather-to-san-antonio |title=Welcome to Night Vale Brings Eldritch Weather to San Antonio |work=San Antonio Current |date=2017-11-24 |accessdate=2018-09-27 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Biese |first=Alex |url=https://www.app.com/story/entertainment/events/fan-theory/2018/09/10/mal-blum-tour-welcome-night-vale-spy-desert-podcast/1223538002/ |title=Mal Blum on tour with Welcome to Night Vale for A Spy in the Desert |work=app. |publisher=USA Today |date=2018-09-10 |accessdate=2018-09-27 }}</ref>.
They have contributed non-musical written work to [[Autostraddle]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Mal Blum|url=http://www.autostraddle.com/author/malblum/|website=Autostraddle}}</ref> ''[[Huffington Post]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/mal-blum/|title=Mal Blum - HuffPost|website=www.huffingtonpost.com}}</ref> and ''[[The Fader]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefader.com/2014/12/17/nine-diy-venues|title=10 NYC DIY Venues That Closed This Year And Why We’ll Miss Them|website=The FADER}}</ref>
Blum attended [[State University of New York at Purchase]].
